<h3>Summary</h3>

<p style="margin-left: 1cm">Due to the success and dissemination of Linux the idea of Open Source Software (OSS) is now known in industry as well as in the public. The BerliOS Open Source Center shall support and mediate between interests and needs of the different groups (like developers, users, distributors, support companies, etc.) and to promote dissemination of this market model. The main objective of BerliOS is to increase the level of awareness and to support deployment through mediation between free developers, commercial providers (e.g. software manufacturers, support companies) and users (e.g. small and mid-size enterprises as well as the public administration).

